paragraph_text: Titanium is a metal that has some unique qualities that make it very desirable as a frame material for bicycles. It just will not rust in any normal atmospheric conditions, or with road salt, or if scratched, dented or damaged. It doesn’t need painting or coating and doesn’t suffer at all from fatigue cracking. It is really comfortable to ride, with a perfect ratio of stiffness, strength and durability. Of course, it’s more expensive than steel, but then it will last a very very long time. It’s also much lighter – a Titanium Cargo frame can weigh nearly 2 kilos less than the standard steel version.

We offer the Omnium Cargo, Omnium Mini-Max and CXC models in standard Titanium versions, and although these will follow the geometry and sizing of the standard steel models we use upsized and specially shaped tubing to increase further the durability of the bike and create a legacy frame that you can pound into the ground and still keep on riding.

We can also offer further custom options such as fittings for Gates Belt Drive, Rohloff hub dropouts, sliding drop outs, geometry adjustments, extra clearance etc. Basically if you can describe it we can build it for you. We are happy to hear from you to discuss your needs.

Our titanium versions are a bike messenger and world touring favourite. Titanium CXCs have twice won the Bike Messenger World Championships and been on some amazing tours in far-flung corners of the globe. We hope your custom Omnium will take you somewhere cool too.
It seems we can’t find what you’re looking for. Perhaps searching can help.

Want to be a messenger when you grow up? Want to bring all your mud pies to the table? Found a stick that weighs 80 kilos that you MUST have at home in your bed? We are here for you. Built just like the adulting Cargo but a bit lower so that your current legs will reach the ground. Pass it on.
We offer complete bikes, fully assembled and ready to ride from our
and have your bike delivered WORLDWIDE with only minor assembly tasks left. We also offer frame-sets too so you can build your dream Omnium.
Recommended maximum loading weight including rider: 175 kg

We design and build fast, light and stable cargo bikes and messenger bikes for packages, people and travel. We are dedicated to making Cargo bikes of the highest quality and to constantly innovating and improving our products and service.
Omnium Cargo is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

Jimmi is a World Champion bike messenger legend, creator of the Omnium company and the designer of all our models – drawing on nearly two decades experience as a bike messenger to make Omnium bikes the toughest, fastest and most practical anywhere.
The Copenhagen shop manager and the best Omnium mechanic you’ll find. Master of the vast shop hound, ex-bike messenger and blessed with twice the energy of a normal human. Also a master chef.
Ex-messenger/dispatcher and now webshop backroom guru, packing n’ shipping like a boss. Fastest box-taper in town. Also acting as an all-round sales guy in the shop.
Our amazing apprentice mechanic and salesperson. Learning fast, and soon ready to take over the world.
Master of the internet and everything floating around in it. Nobody has ventured further into the WordPress forest and emerged alive.
Graphic designer and Omnium identity creator.
– visit our official store for direct sales and test rides.
We offer many ways for you to get your Omnium on. The best route is to see if there is a dealer near you. See our
for our list of dealers worldwide. That way you can test our bikes and get excellent service. If you don’t have a nearby dealer or want to order direct then please get in touch
. If you are buying from outside Denmark and you have a company VAT number then we can help you deduct VAT. Please email us.

As a result of our drive to make the absolute best messenger cargo bike on the planet – lighter, faster, and more agile than the competition, we now offer a full custom consulting service. In collaboration with our design and manufacturing team we can provide pedal vehicles with custom paint, racks, bags, boxes, graphic design, Shimano STEPS 8000 Electric System and even complete custom frame design. All made in our own production chain and shipped worldwide. From a single bike to a national fleet that fits the image and unique needs of your business – we can do it. No compromise.

We can also provide educational and consultancy support for business studies and manufacturing. Book a seminar and learn about how a successful bike business gets started and how it works in the real world – from its founder. Please get in touch to start the conversation.

We offer complete bikes, fully assembled and ready to ride from our
and have your bike delivered WORLDWIDE.
More info on the STEPS system see:

The powerful SHIMANO STEPS motor is strong enough to handle the steepest of hills, yet intuitive enough to give you just the right amount of support for every pedal stroke along the way. Designed specifically to give you the natural feel of riding a normal bike. Weighs only 2.8kg, one of the lightest motors on the market. Stable, smooth intuitive power for improved bike handling over every part of your day. Solidly supports speeds up to 25 km/h.

Lightweight yet rigid crankset for direct power transfer. Both crankset and the rest of the drivetrain are built on SHIMANO’s proven technology. This gives you reliability and confidence from first to last pedal stroke. Drivetrain components are designed to work in sync with each other for unparalleled effectiveness and reliability. Spec’d with SHIMANO Hollowtech II bottom bracket for added strength and direct power transfer. E-bike specific Deore XT crankset. A 165 mm crank arm minimises pedal strikes and maintains smooth cadence and motor assistance.

Extensive choice of power-assist settings to match your unique riding style. Compact, easy-to-read display with dynamic visuals when switching between support settings. Further personalise your support settings by choosing Dynamic, Explorer or Custom Mode to perfectly match your riding style and intended terrain. The computer is specifically designed to be compact and also durable for bad weather riding. Easy-to-read LCD – each support setting assigned a unique colour. Sleek bar-mounted computer with dynamic LCD display shows gear number, power assist mode and battery range information. Wirelessly customise your preferences via Bluetooth.

Ultra-durable, replaceable, powerful battery specially designed for the rigours of cargo biking. Low profile design for improved impact and vibration resistance. High capacity long-lasting Li-Ion battery of 504 Wh to cover more territory. Supported travel up to 100 km on one charge. 1,000 charge cycles with no significant power loss.
Recommended maximum loading weight including rider: 175 kg

The Omnium CXC is a super-sharp and versatile bike with all sorts of possibilities. This bike can do pretty much anything you need it to. A Mixte version means you can wear a skirt and still shred the streets. Gravel, cyclocross, world tour, alleycat or commute suit – we can make the CXC work for you. And now with the possibility of a carbon fork upgrade to cut grams and stiffen the steering for offroad applications. We can fit full mudguards and all the front and back racks you’ll need to portage your gear in safety – or leave it naked for full-speed operation. There is nothing more versatile.

Keep it in the family! Add our nylon cargo webbing to provide a super-strong surface that can hold crazy loads all day long.

Omnium Cargo uses cookies according to the new Electronic Communications Act, which came into force on 25 July 2003. A cookie is a small text file stored on your computer that contains information that helps the website to identify and track the visitor. Cookies do no harm to your computer, consist only of text, can not contain viruses and occupies virtually no space on your hard drive. There are two types of cookies: “Session Cookies” and cookies that are saved permanently on your computer.

The first type of cookie commonly used is “Session Cookies”. During the time you visit the website, our web server assigns your browser a unique identifier string so as not to confuse you with other visitors. A “Session Cookie” is never stored permanently on your computer and disappears when you close your browser. To use Omnium Cargo without troubles you need to have cookies enabled.

The second type of cookie saves a file permanently on your computer. This type of cookie is used to track how visitors move around on the website. This is only used to offer visitors better services and support. The text files can be deleted. On Omnium Cargo we use this type of cookie to keep track of your shopping cart and to keep statistics of our visitors. The information stored on your computer is only a unique number, without any connection to personal information.

Omnium Cargo reserves the right to amend any information, including but not limited to prices, technical specifications, terms of purchase and product offerings without prior notice. At the event of when a product is sold out, Omnium Cargo has the right to cancel the order and refund any amount paid in the best way. It is really comfortable to ride, with a perfect ratio of stiffness, strength and durability. Of course, it’s more expensive than steel, but then it will last a very very long time. After a series of prototypes and a lot of adjustments we are proud to announce our first official child seat product. We have always admired the Thule Yepp Maxi seat, it is comfortable and safe – a market leader too. They are everywhere in Denmark. So we made a burly aluminium bracket which bolts under the rack of the Omnium Cargo and fits the Thule Yepp Maxi seat perfectly.
The Thule Yepp Maxi EasyFit seat has a super-safe key-locked metal base which slots directly into our bracket.

To fit the bracket just remove the four bolts holding on your rack, position the bracket on the frame tabs that hold the rack, put the rack back on and replace the standard bolts with the (supplied) longer bolts.
Then simply fit the Thule Yepp Maxi ‘EasyFit’ seat as per their instructions and connect the safety strap. The whole procedure takes around 10 mins.

Once fitted the first time you can easily install or remove the seat in less than a minute.
